#!/bin/sh
cat <<'EOF'
IBM 5251 Dvorak Layout  (5250_DVORAK)
======================================

NUMBER ROW  unshifted: ESC  &  [  {  (  =  *  )  +  ]  !  #  `
              shifted:   $  %  7  5  3  1  9  0  2  4  6  8  ~

ALPHA (Dvorak positions)
  Row2: ;  ,  .  p  y  f  g  c  r  l  /  =
  Row3: a  o  e  u  i  d  h  t  n  s  -
  Row4: '  q  j  k  x  b  m  w  v  z

MODIFIERS
  CapsLock = sticky Ctrl: press CapsLock, then one key -> Ctrl+key
  Alt      = one-shot (press Alt then key)
  Shift    = hold (two shift keys, both sides)

NUMPAD ARROWS (press Alt first, then numpad key)
  Alt+8 = Up   Alt+4 = Left   Alt+6 = Right   Alt+2 = Down

LEFT-CLUSTER ARROWS  Up/Down/Left/Right (when discovered & mapped)

SPECIAL KEYS
  ESC    = leftmost key above Tab  (was backtick)
  F1/F2  = ESC as well
  Ctrl+C = CapsLock then c     Ctrl+Z = CapsLock then z
  Tab    = Tab key              Backspace = Backspace key
EOF
